ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported
Autism; PDD-NOS; Asperger's; ADHD; Language Disorder; Other; None

ElementDescription: Patient Course After Emergency Department [1 = Admitted]
Notes: 1=Discharged; 2=Admitted to observation for less than 12 hours for social reasons (e.g., Can't get a ride home, arranging housing); 3=Admitted to observation for less than 12 hours for clinical reasons; 4=Admitted to observation for greater than 12 hours

ElementDescription: Patient Procedure: Laceration Repair. Number of times
Patient Procedure: Fracture Reduction. Number of times
Patient Procedure: Bladder Catheter. Number of times
Patient Procedure: Incision and Drain. Number of times
Patient Procedure: Lumbar Puncture. Number of times
Patient Procedure: Diagnostic peritoneal lavage. Number of times
Patient is admitted following ED evaluation
Notes: 0 = patient was discharged from ED; 1 = Patient was admitted

ElementDescription: Patient is admitted following ED evaluation; fully imputed from F1b cohort
Notes: 0 = patient was discharged from ED; 1 = Patient was admitted
